					<head>Talmud Yerushalmi</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
						<summary>Volume 2 of a portion of the Palestinian Talmud, with a commentary by Solomon ben Joseph Sirillo.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="tmr-Hebr">Aramaic, Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
							<locus from="1r" to="367v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Talmud yerushalmi</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">תלמוד ירושלמי</title>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Lehmann_1875"/>
								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
							<filiation>Uniform with Or 2822 and Or 2824, <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">403</ref>  and <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">405</ref> (volume 1 and 3 of this manuscript, respectively).</filiation>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="1r" to="106v"/>
								<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sheviʿit </title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="106v" to="201r"/>
								<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Terumot</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="201r" to="238r"/>
								<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Maʿaserot </title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="238r" to="291v"/>
								<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Maʿaser sheni</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="292r" to="293r"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Notes</title>
								<note>
									<p>Some verses and notes in different hands of apparently the 17th century. Folios 292r-293r contain some poetical pieces. The name Yisra᾿el is marked off as an acrostic.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="294r" to="311r"/>
								<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Masekhet Sheviʿit (ha-῾oteḳ ha-sheni)</title>
								<note>
									<p>Partly written in an Oriental hand. </p>
									<p>Contains the entire first chapter, and a fragment of the second chapter. </p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="311r" to="367v"/>
								<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Masekhet Demaʾi (ha-῾oteḳ ha-sheni)</title>
								<note>
									<p>The last chapter is imperfect at the end.</p>
									<p>There is a lacuna after folio 367.</p>
									<p>In the margin of folios 316r-317v there are several poetical pieces, in which the name Yisra᾿el is marked off as an acrostic.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<note>
								<p>See also <ref target="FJB" type="number">16</ref> (1988), pp. 53-73.</p>
							</note>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/33429759">Sirillo, Solomon ben Joseph, approximately 1558</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/33429759">סיריליאו, שלמה בן יוסף</persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex; Sefardi square and semi-cursive script of the 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex.</support>
								<extent>367  folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>300</height>
										<width>205</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>215</height>
										<width>140</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>367 folios (+ 2 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
									<p>Hebrew foliation added in a later cursive hand in the upper left-hand corner of each recto.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of originally 8 leaves each.</p>
									<p>No catchwords.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Leaves missing after folio 367.</p>
									<p>A number of pages stained or damaged.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 2" ruledLines="40" writtenLines="40">
									<p>The number of the semi-cursive writing is usually 40, but that of the square writing (on the inner part of the page) varies considerably.</p>
									<p>Many marginal notes and comments supplied in various cursive hands.</p>
									<p>Running titles.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="4">
							<summary>Sefardi square and semi-cursive script of the 16th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Ye᾿udah Zeraḥyah Azula᾿i</name>: inscribed in a purchase note, folio 1r, and in the lower margin of folio 368v.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Post-1600. Black leather.</p>
								<p>Spine title: 'Talmud Jerushalmi. Hebrew. Vol. II. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2823.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
